race.description: Landcruiser King Of The Road Handicap (Bm58+)
race.comment: BELVEDERE ROCK (3) scored the hat-trick here last start when running away to win easily once again, scoring by 1.6L. He steps up to 1900m for the first time today, but that doesn't look an issue. Will need some luck from the gate but he looks above average and can continue his winning ways. MASTER ALEX (4) was only 1.8L off the winner last start at Ascot and will find this much easier as he returns to Geraldton. Up in trip for the first time today, but he's racing in good order and rates highly on his recent efforts. DESERT EDGE (6) went close last start over 1920m at York in an easier race last start but drops in weight today. He has the speed to be up front from the barrier and if he's able to dictate the speed, he'll be tough to reel in. MYSTICAL MAN (2) gets the tongue tie on now and creates interest coming back to this grade today. NEVER SOBER (9) is racing well and can feature up in trip.
